A person was arrested after an hourslong standoff Saturday afternoon and evening in St. Louis Park, after police said he was shooting arrows at a house. Just after 1 p.m. Saturday, St. Louis Park police went to the 1400 block of Flag Avenue South after someone said a person was shooting arrows at a neighbor's house. The person had barricaded himself in his home when police arrived. A SWAT team was called to the neighborhood around 2 p.m. City officials said just after 7 p.m. that the SWAT team was talking to the person who barricaded himself inside the house, and was trying to use "non-lethal methods" to get him out. According to the city, the person was taken into custody around 10:30 p.m. Saturday. No one was hurt, according to city officials.